    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-05-30T14:31:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-05-30T14:31:00-05:00" n="564"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss> files, lot 55 D 338, “South Korean Attitude
                    Toward Armistice, May 1953”</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of Staff United States Army (<persName
                            corresp="#p_CGJL1" type="from">Collins</persName>) to the Commander in
                        Chief Far East (<persName corresp="#p_CGMW1" type="to"
                        >Clark</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>emergency</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-05-30T15:31:00-04:00"
                            >May 30, 1953—3:31 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_DA1">DA</gloss> 940242. From <gloss target="#t_CSUSA1"
                        >CSUSA</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_CINCUNC1">CINCUNC</gloss> exclusive for
                        <persName corresp="#p_RMGCL1">Gen Clark</persName> ref our <gloss
                        target="#t_DA1">DA</gloss> 940238<note n="1" xml:id="d564fn1">Dated May 29,
                            <ref target="#pg_1119">p. 1119</ref>.</note> and your CX 62747.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d564fn2">Dated May 30, <ref target="#pg_1120">p.
                        1120</ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss> have authorized me to transmit following:
                        <pb facs="1158" n="1124" xml:id="pg_1124"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Consideration has just been given to current difficulties with <gloss
                                target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Government and your plan “<gloss
                                target="#t_EVERREADY1">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Everready</hi>
                            </gloss>”.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>We cannot concur with any action on your part which would establish a
                                <gloss target="#t_UNC1">UNC</gloss> military government in <gloss
                                target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>. However in event of internal <gloss
                                target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> political or military disaffection
                            against present <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Government, you as
                            the responsible military commander will take whatever other steps you
                            deem appropriate to safeguard the integrity and security of your
                            forces.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Instructions re the offer to <persName corresp="#p_RS1"
                                >Rhee</persName> of a bilateral security pact are contained in
                            separate radio<note n="3" xml:id="d564fn3">Telegram <gloss
                                    target="#t_DA1">DA</gloss> 940241, <hi rend="italic">
                                    <ref target="#d564">supra</ref>
                                </hi>.</note> dispatched simultaneously.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
